<item>
            <title>[LU-17861] conf-sanity test_103:  Fail to rename OST 5</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17861</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e336f909-cd2c-4878-a94c-3fcec72dcb98&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/e336f909-cd2c-4878-a94c-3fcec72dcb98&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has been failing intermittently since 2024-02-25, about 10x in 13 weeks. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_103 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;(9) Fail to rename OST 5
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4504&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4504&lt;/a&gt; - 5.14.21-150500.55.39-default&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4504&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4504&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.27.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like there is a problem with the OST filesystem still being mounted:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;CMD: trevis-95vm3 tunefs.lustre --fsname=lustre --rename=tfs -v /dev/mapper/ost1_flakey
trevis-95vm3: /dev/mapper/ost1_flakey: is currently mounted, exiting without any change
checking for existing Lustre data: found

   Read previous values:
Target:     tfs-OST0000
Index:      0
Lustre FS:  tfs
Mount type: ldiskfs
Flags:      0x2
              (OST )
Persistent mount opts: ,errors=remount-ro
Parameters: mgsnode=10.240.43.222@tcp sys.timeout=20


   Permanent disk data:
Target:     lustre-OST0000
Index:      0
Lustre FS:  lustre
Mount type: ldiskfs
Flags:      0x2
              (OST )
Persistent mount opts: ,errors=remount-ro
Parameters: mgsnode=10.240.43.222@tcp sys.timeout=20

 conf-sanity test_103: @@@@@@ FAIL: (9) Fail to rename OST 1 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;





&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
conf-sanity test_103 - (9) Fail to rename OST 5&lt;/p&gt;</description>
